The article announces several presidential nominations that have been sent to the Senate. Leslie E. Bains has been nominated to be a Director of the Securities Investor Protection Corporation, Tony Hammond has been reappointed as a Commissioner of the Postal Regulatory Commission, and Caroline Kennedy has been nominated to be Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to Japan. Additionally, Marcel J. Lettre II has been nominated to be a Principal Deputy Under Secretary of Defense, Donald Lu has been nominated to be Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the Republic of Albania, Robert A. Sherman has been nominated to be Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the Portuguese Republic, and Robert Michael Simon has been nominated to be an Associate Director of the Office of Science and Technology Policy.